Radiation in deep space that can be hazardous for a potential Moon/Mars mission consists of omnipresent highly energetic GCRs, sporadic and possibly highly intense SEPs, and secondary radiation as primary particles (either GCRs or SEPs) pass through the spacecraft hull or the planetary atmosphere. SEPs and GCRs have different origins, properties, and distributions in space and time.Fig. 1
